35 "(b) The felony of child abuse is an offense additional to other civil and criminal
36 provisions and is not intended to repeal or preclude any other sanctions or remedies.
37 (c) Abandonment of an infant less than 30 days of age pursuant to G.S. 14-322.3 may be
38 treated as a mitigating factor in sentencing for a conviction under this section involving that
39 infant.
40 (d) The following definitions apply in this section:
41 (1) Grossly negligent omission. – In the context of providing care to or
42 supervision of a child, this term includes the failure to report a child as missing
43 to law enforcement as provided in G.S. 14-318.5(b).";

